The defamation case that African National Congress (ANC) Member of Parliament Derek Hanekom has brought against former President Jacob Zuma will be heard in the High Court in Durban on Friday. Hanekom, who’s also a member of the ANC’s National Executive Committee, is suing Zuma for R500 000 for claiming that he was a known enemy agent. Hanekom, who now wants Zuma to compensate him, is arguing that the accusations have caused immense harm and damage to his reputation. Zuma has indicated his intention to oppose the case. Click on related video below: 